## Part 2 — Deploy to Railway

**Step 5** — Go to **railway.app** → click **Login** → **Login with GitHub** → authorize

**Step 6** — Click **New Project** → **Deploy from GitHub repo**

**Step 7** — Select `playwright-mcp-server` from your repo list

**Step 8** — Railway auto-detects everything. Click **Deploy now**

**Step 9** — Wait about 3–4 minutes for the build. You'll see logs streaming. Wait until you see:
```
Playwright MCP Server running on port XXXX
```

**Step 10** — Click on your deployment → go to **Settings** tab → under **Networking** click **Generate Domain**

You'll get a URL like:
```
https://playwright-mcp-server-production.up.railway.app
```

**Copy that URL** — you'll need it in the next part.

---

## Part 3 — Connect to Agile Insights

**Step 11** — Go back to Agile Insights → open your agent → go to the MCP tool editor (the screen you showed me)

**Step 12** — Set:
- **Transport Type:** `SSE`
- **MCP Server URL:** `https://YOUR-RAILWAY-URL.up.railway.app/sse`

(Replace `YOUR-RAILWAY-URL` with what Railway gave you)

**Step 13** — Click **Save / Deploy**

